    // Section 1: Hero Narrative
    "ah.hero_title": "Professional Air Hostess & Cabin Crew Training in Vadodara",
    "ah.hero_p1": "The skies have always captured human imagination. For many young aspirants across Gujarat—from Surat to Rajkot, from Ahmedabad to Vadodara—the dream of donning that immaculate cabin crew uniform and walking down the aisle at 35,000 feet is a powerful motivator. But let us be absolutely clear from the outset: becoming a professional **air hostess** or **cabin crew member** is not merely about glamour. It is about rigorous training, split-second decision-making during emergencies, and the ability to deliver exceptional service under pressure.",
    "ah.hero_p2": "At **Wings Institute, Vadodara**—Gujarat's oldest and largest aviation training institute since 2008—we have trained thousands of young men and women who now fly with prestigious carriers including **Qatar Airways, Singapore Airlines, Emirates, Indigo Airlines, Air India, and Vistara**. Our approach is fundamentally different from certificate-churning factories: we focus on *career outcomes*, not just course completion.",
    "ah.wings_advantage_title": "The Wings Advantage: In-House Airbus A330 Mock Cabin",
    "ah.wings_advantage_intro": "We are the **only institute in Gujarat** with a full-scale **Airbus A330 mock aircraft** on campus. This is not a scaled model or a photograph—it is a fully functional training simulator where you will conduct:",
    "ah.advantage_safety": "**Safety Drills:** Water evacuation procedures for emergency landing scenarios on water bodies",
    "ah.advantage_evacuation": "**Emergency Evacuation:** 90-second evacuation protocols, slide deployment, and passenger crowd management",
    "ah.advantage_fire": "**Fire Fighting Drills:** Using fire extinguishers, smoke hoods, and containment procedures at altitude",
    "ah.advantage_pa": "**PA Announcements:** Professional voice modulation for in-flight announcements in English and Hindi",
    "ah.advantage_meal": "**Meal Service Simulation:** Using actual airline trolleys to master in-flight service protocols",
    "ah.hero_p3": "Why does this matter? Because airlines do not hire candidates who have only read textbooks. During your airline interview—whether at **Ahmedabad International Airport** or Mumbai—you will be tested on practical scenarios. Students who have physically practised safety drills and emergency evacuation in a realistic environment consistently outperform those who have not. This is the difference between theoretical knowledge and *muscle memory* that kicks in during high-pressure situations.",
    "ah.hero_p4": "If you are searching for the **best cabin crew training institute in Gujarat** or comparing **air hostess training course fees in Vadodara**, understand that the value lies not in the certificate alone, but in the infrastructure, faculty expertise, and placement track record that backs it.",

    // Section 2: Eligibility
    "ah.elig_title": "Who Can Apply? Eligibility Criteria for Cabin Crew",
    "ah.elig_intro": "This is where we address the real anxieties that keep young aspirants awake at night. We receive dozens of calls every week asking: *\"Am I too short?\"*, *\"I have some acne scars—will I be rejected?\"*, *\"I only studied till 12th—can I still become an air hostess?\"* Let us address each concern with honesty and practical guidance.",
    "ah.height_title": "Height Requirements: The Real Picture",
    "ah.height_intro": "Height is perhaps the most-searched eligibility criterion for aspiring cabin crew. Here is the reality: different airlines have different requirements, and there is more flexibility than most candidates assume.",
    "ah.height_female": "**Females:** Most domestic Indian airlines (Indigo, Air India, SpiceJet) require a minimum height of **155 cm (5'1\")**. International carriers like Emirates and Qatar Airways require **160 cm** or an arm-reach of **212 cm** while standing on tiptoes.",
    "ah.height_male": "**Males:** The minimum height for male cabin crew is typically **170 cm (5'7\")** for domestic airlines. International carriers may require **173-175 cm**.",
    "ah.height_reassurance": "**Reassurance for borderline candidates:** If you are within 1-2 cm of the minimum requirement, do not lose hope. Our grooming module includes **posture correction exercises** and techniques that can add up to 1-2 cm to your standing height. Proper posture, heel selection, and confidence during arm-reach tests have helped many of our students clear airline assessments.",
    "ah.skin_title": "Skin & Complexion: Addressing Sensitive Concerns",
    "ah.skin_intro": "Let us be direct: airlines look for a **clear, well-maintained complexion**—not perfection. Minor acne scars, birthmarks, or skin imperfections that can be concealed with standard makeup are generally acceptable. The key concerns airlines screen for are:",
    "ah.skin_item1": "Visible tattoos on exposed areas (face, neck, hands, lower arms)",
    "ah.skin_item2": "Severe scarring that cannot be concealed with foundation",
    "ah.skin_item3": "Active skin conditions that may be contagious",
    "ah.skin_p2": "At Wings Institute, our **in-house spa and skincare module** teaches you daily routines using natural home remedies. We also have **professional makeup stations** with hi-luminous mirrors where you practise the exact airline-standard makeup routine every single day. By the time you graduate, concealing minor imperfections becomes second nature.",
    "ah.edu_title": "Educational Qualification: The 12th Pass Advantage",
    "ah.edu_p1": "Here is excellent news for students who cannot afford or do not wish to pursue a 4-year degree: the minimum educational requirement for cabin crew positions is **12th Pass (10+2)** from a recognised board. This makes the cabin crew career path one of the most accessible high-paying professions for young Indians.",
    "ah.edu_p2": "However, do not mistake \"accessible\" for \"easy.\" Airlines receive lakhs of applications for a few hundred positions. What differentiates successful candidates is professional training, grooming, communication skills, and safety knowledge—precisely what we provide at Wings Institute.",
